Accuracy and reproducibility of the assay were established basing on the C
T values obtained from testing DNA standards in triplicates; within each run (intra-assay) and in three consecutive runs (inter-assay) (Table 3
). The calculated S.D and C.V values for intra-assay variability were low, ranging from 0.03 to 0.53 and from 0.13% to 1.25%, respectively. The inter-assay variability was slightly higher with S.D ranged from 0.07 to 0.51 and C.V ranged from 0.22% to 2.5%.
